{
  "stem": "23942.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I was so rich when I had these grandparents.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I felt so rich when I had them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was the most happiest memories, just go to visit them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You see--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You see, the typical Shabbos was like this.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was somewhat spoiled because my father's presence wasn't there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But my mother kept up everything that was in her power to keep up.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She baked the challahs on Friday herself.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She baked the rugelach, which I can still smell and see in front of my eyes.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I-- and right-- and she, she cleaned up the house.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was Shabbistic.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was beautiful.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- and then she would sit down and write a letter to my father and sometimes to her aunt.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And this is-- Shabbos was quiet and peaceful.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the village was-- assumed a beautiful-- Jewish people lived, you know, a few hundred.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it was quiet.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And, and the goyim didn't-- knew that the Jews are Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they go to shul with stramel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You see men with stramel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I have a picture here, I have a book which shows how it looked, Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It-- what I don't remember, it describes in this book.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Because this-- Mr.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Beller, the painter painted what Shabbos looks like in Grodzisko.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So he-- he confirmed what I remember.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Shabbos was quiet.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "There was no noise.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "There was-- there were no cars.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And the few-- you hardly saw a horse or a wagon.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And people walked in the middle of the street to go to shul in the morning.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "In the afternoon, they carried the cholent, and it smelled in the streets.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "You walked-- you walked to the baker.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I used to pick up the cholent with my sister.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And it smelled like heaven.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
